---
import BlockOffLayout from '../../layouts/BlockOffLayout.astro';
---

<BlockOffLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Block OFF"
  description="Read the Block OFF Privacy Policy for our AI comment moderation tool for YouTube and Instagram creators."
  canonicalPath="/blockoff/privacy"
>
  <header class="site-header page-header">
    <a class="brand" href="/blockoff" aria-label="Block OFF home"><img src="/blockoff/block-off-logo.png" alt="" /><span>Block OFF</span></a>
    <nav class="main-nav" aria-label="Primary navigation">
      <a href="/blockoff/#product">Product</a>
      <a href="/blockoff/#how">How it works</a>
      <a href="/blockoff/#dashboard">Dashboard</a>
      <a href="/blockoff/#pricing">Pricing</a>
    </nav>
    <a class="header-cta" href="/blockoff/#waitlist">Join waitlist</a>
  </header>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <span class="section-kicker">Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>Last updated: July 7, 2026. This page explains what Block OFF may collect, why we collect it, and how creator data is protected.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="legal-layout">
      <nav class="legal-nav" aria-label="Privacy sections">
        <a href="#overview">Overview</a>
        <a href="#data">Data we collect</a>
        <a href="#use">How we use data</a>
        <a href="#sharing">Sharing</a>
        <a href="#retention">Retention</a>
        <a href="#rights">Your rights</a>
      </nav>
      <article class="legal-content">
        <section id="overview">
          <h2>Overview</h2>
          <p>Block OFF is being built as an AI comment moderation tool for YouTube and Instagram creators. To provide scanning, hiding, review, analytics, and restoration features, the product may need limited access to connected account data and comments that you authorize us to process.</p>
          <p>We do not want to collect more data than the product needs. Our goal is to process only the information required to detect harmful comments, show moderation decisions, and help you manage your community.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="data">
          <h2>Data we collect</h2>
          <p>Depending on the features you use, Block OFF may collect account information such as your name, email address, connected platform profile, profile ID, OAuth authorization status, and billing or launch offer status.</p>
          <p>When you purchase the launch offer, payment checkout is handled by Dodo Payments. Block OFF may receive payment status, product, amount, email, and transaction reference information, but full card details are handled by the payment provider and are not stored by Block OFF.</p>
          <p>Block OFF may also process comment data such as comment text, author display name, platform comment ID, post or video ID, moderation score, rule triggers, action taken, timestamps, and whether a comment was hidden, allowed, restored, or marked for review.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="use">
          <h2>How we use data</h2>
          <p>We use data to provide the service, including scanning comments, detecting spam, scams, harassment, hate, and toxic language, applying user-defined moderation rules, showing analytics, and maintaining an activity log.</p>
          <p>We may also use contact information to send product updates, support replies, security notices, billing confirmations, and launch access details.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="sharing">
          <h2>Sharing and processors</h2>
          <p>Block OFF may use infrastructure, database, authentication, analytics, payment, and AI moderation providers to operate the product. For launch-offer checkout and subscription payments, Block OFF uses Dodo Payments as a payment provider. These providers process data only so the service can function.</p>
          <p>We do not sell creator comment data. We do not use your private moderation data to build public creator profiles. We may disclose information if required by law, to protect users, or to enforce our Terms and Conditions.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="retention">
          <h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
          <p>We keep data only as long as needed to provide the service, meet legal obligations, resolve disputes, prevent abuse, and maintain product records. Creators should be able to request deletion of their account and associated moderation history.</p>
          <p>Some records may remain in backups for a limited period before automatic deletion. We may also retain minimal transaction records when required for tax, fraud prevention, or accounting purposes.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="rights">
          <h2>Your rights</h2>
          <p>You may contact us to request access, correction, export, or deletion of personal information associated with your Block OFF account. You can also disconnect social accounts when you no longer want Block OFF to scan or moderate comments.</p>
          <p>For privacy questions, contact <a href="mailto:hello@blockoff.app">hello@blockoff.app</a>.</p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
  <footer class="site-footer">
    <a class="brand footer-brand" href="/blockoff" aria-label="Block OFF home"><img src="/blockoff/block-off-logo.png" alt="" /><span>Block OFF</span></a>
    <nav aria-label="Footer navigation">
      <a href="/blockoff/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
      <a href="/blockoff/terms">Terms & Conditions</a>
      <a href="/blockoff/about">About Us</a>
      <a href="/blockoff/contact">Contact Us</a>
      <a href="/blockoff/support">Support</a>
      <a href="/blockoff/changelog">Changelog</a>
    </nav>
  </footer>
</BlockOffLayout>
